Finland s Henri Kontinen and Australia s John Peers triumphed in the doubles final at the Barclays ATP World Tour Finals at the O2 Arena in London, United Kingdom, Sunday, when they defeated Raven Klaasen, of South Africa, and Rajeev Ram, of the United States. The two first-year pairings were contesting after Klaasen and Ram surprised newly crowned world No 1 doubles side Jamie Murray and Bruno Soares on Saturday. The event is spectacular. The venue is spectacular. The fans are great. Having our family here has been spectacular and then, of course, winning matches helps too, Klaasen said ahead of the match. African News Agency (ANA)